Executive Profile
Peter G. Leemputte  Director, MCBC Holdings, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 7 different industries.See Board Relationships60--
Background

		Mr. Peter G. Leemputte, also known as Pete, served as the Chief Financial Officer and Treasurer at Keurig Green Mountain, Inc. since August 17, 2015 until May 2016. Mr. Leemputte served as the Chief Financial Officer of Mead Johnson Nutrition Company from September 2008 to March 13, 2015 and served as its Executive Vice President from January 2012 to March 13, 2015. He served as Senior Vice President at Mead Johnson Nutrition Company from September 2008 to December 2011. ... He served as a Senior Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of Brunswick Corporation from September 22, 2003 to September 2008. He served as Principal Accounting Officer of Brunswick Corp. and also served as its Vice President and Controller from 2001 to September 22, 2003. Mr. Leemputte served as an Executive Vice President and Chief Administrative Officer of Chicago Title and Trust Company since January 1998 and its Chief Financial Officer since March 1998. He served as the Chief Administrative Officer and Chief Financial Officer of Chicago Title Insurance Company since January 1998 and March 1998 respectively. He served as the Chief Administrative Officer, Chief Financial Officer and Executive Vice President of Chicago Title Corporation from 1998 to 2000. He served as Vice President and Partner of Mercer Management Consulting Inc. from July 1996 to January 1998 and served as Corporate Vice President and Controller of Armco Inc. He joined CT&T from Mercer Management Consulting, where his focus was on operational and financial improvement and where he led the CT&T's efforts to identify best practices in managing economic cycles in process industries. His career also includes domestic and international financial assignments with Armco Inc., and BP Amoco. Mr. Leemputte spent five years with Amoco Corp., where he served as Head of the financial analysis unit in its Treasury group. He joined FMC Corp., where he served as both Head of operations analysis and group controller. In Armco Inc., he spent three years as corporate controller. He also served as a Product Development Engineer with Procter & Gamble Company. He has been a Director at Beazer Homes USA Inc. since August 3, 2005. He serves on the National Council of Washington University in St. Louis School of Engineering and Applied Science. He serves on the Advisory Board of the Washington University School of Engineering in St. Louis. He is a seasoned Industry Executive and has more than 30 years of financial management experience. Mr. Leemputte holds a Bachelor of Science degree in Chemical Engineering from Washington University, St. Louis and a Master of Business Administration in Finance and Marketing from the University of Chicago Graduate School of Business.Read Full Background




