Peter G. Leemputte

Executive Vice President  and Chief Financial Officer



Peter G. Leemputte
Executive Vice President  and Chief Financial Officer
Age: 59
Peter Leemputte was appointed executive vice president and chief financial officer in January 2012. He joined Mead Johnson in 2008 as senior vice president and chief financial officer.
From 2003 to 2008, Mr. Leemputte served as senior vice president and chief financial officer of Brunswick Corporation, a manufacturer of recreation and leisure-time products. Prior to joining Brunswick, he was executive vice president and chief financial and administrative officer with Chicago Title Corporation, a leading publicly traded national service provider offering residential and commercial title insurance. His previous experience includes serving as a partner in Mercer Management Consulting's global practice covering strategy and operational studies; and domestic and international financial assignments with Armco Inc., FMC Corporation and BP Amoco. He also served as a product development engineer with Procter & Gamble Company.
He serves on the Board of Directors of Beazer Homes USA, Inc., and on the Advisory Board of the Washington University School of Engineering in St. Louis.
Born and raised in the Chicago area, Mr. Leemputte holds an MBA in finance from the University of Chicago Booth School of Business and a bachelor's in chemical engineering from Washington University in St. Louis.




















